WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:09.139
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

00:11.000 --> 00:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:19.236 --> 00:22.152
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

00:36.732 --> 00:39.778
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

00:42.781 --> 00:44.087
[ SOFT THUD ]

01:24.258 --> 01:27.043
I've wanted this for so long.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.653
[ GLASS BREAKING ]

01:33.136 --> 01:36.313
Wait. Wait.

01:36.357 --> 01:38.750
Wait, stop, stop! Huh?

01:38.794 --> 01:41.797
Mary, come on. Oh my god.

01:41.840 --> 01:44.365
I cannot believe I just
did that.

01:44.408 --> 01:47.585
You didn't do anything.

01:47.629 --> 01:50.675
Trevor, I'm married.

01:50.719 --> 01:52.677
Everybody makes mistakes.

01:56.159 --> 01:59.771
Okay... where's your husband
right now?

01:59.815 --> 02:01.773
Not here.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.645
He never is. That's none of your business.

02:03.688 --> 02:07.779
Mary, you deserve someone
who's going to cherish you.

02:07.823 --> 02:09.258
Who'll be there for you.

02:13.872 --> 02:16.179
Everybody makes mistakes.

02:18.834 --> 02:23.099
I was lonely.
We had too much to drink.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.580
Oh, god, we're really good
friends but, Trevor...

02:25.623 --> 02:27.756
we have got... we've gotta
be honest about this.

02:27.799 --> 02:29.758
Don't tell Susan. Trevor!

02:32.804 --> 02:36.678
I know that you may
feel bad about this.

02:36.721 --> 02:40.464
Like it's unfair to Charlie.

02:40.508 --> 02:44.425
But... it's almost 2:00 a.m., at
least part of you has to wonder.

02:44.468 --> 02:48.907
Where's he... who's he with
right now?

02:50.431 --> 02:53.434
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC FADING UP ]

03:16.065 --> 03:20.112
[ GARAGE DOOR OPENING ]

03:20.156 --> 03:21.244
Hello?

03:27.903 --> 03:30.471
Hey. Sorry, I didn't mean
to wake you.

03:30.514 --> 03:32.255
Where were you?

03:32.299 --> 03:34.605
I was working on the house.

03:34.649 --> 03:36.520
You were supposed to come home
for dinner.

03:36.564 --> 03:38.130
I'm sorry, I got hung up.

03:38.174 --> 03:39.349
I'm just gonna jump
in the shower.

03:39.393 --> 03:41.612
You know what today is?

03:41.656 --> 03:43.353
Thursday?

03:43.397 --> 03:45.050
It's our anniversary, Charlie.

03:46.965 --> 03:49.490
Oh, no.

03:49.533 --> 03:52.275
I'm so sorry. I... I just...

03:54.103 --> 03:55.409
Why didn't you...

03:55.452 --> 03:57.759
It was supposed to be
a surprise.

03:57.802 --> 03:59.369
I made you dinner
and then we were gonna...

03:59.413 --> 04:01.850
Hey... let's heat it up.

04:01.893 --> 04:04.592
Right now, come on,
I'm sure it's still good.

04:04.635 --> 04:06.811
Right? You couldn't have eaten
all of it.

04:06.855 --> 04:10.859
No... I...

04:10.902 --> 04:13.557
Susan came over
and had dinner with me.

04:13.601 --> 04:15.211
Susan came over? Did she?

04:15.255 --> 04:18.257
Yeah.

04:18.301 --> 04:20.303
I needed some company.

04:22.087 --> 04:24.002
Okay.

04:26.266 --> 04:28.485
Charlie? Hm?

04:28.529 --> 04:30.792
What happened to your back?

04:30.835 --> 04:33.795
What do you mean? These scratches.

04:33.838 --> 04:36.754
Yeah, I was sliding on my back
under the new cabinets...

04:36.798 --> 04:39.191
and I guess a couple
of the screws aren't flush.

04:39.235 --> 04:41.281
A screw did that?

04:41.324 --> 04:45.197
Yeah, a worksite's a dangerous
place.

04:46.808 --> 04:49.201
Hey.

04:49.245 --> 04:52.596
I'm sorry that I missed dinner.

04:52.640 --> 04:54.555
Let me make it up to you.

04:54.598 --> 04:58.036
I'll make dinner tomorrow,
whatever you want.

04:58.080 --> 05:02.171
The food will not be as good,
but the company will be better.

05:02.214 --> 05:04.086
Then... Susan, right?

05:04.129 --> 05:06.523
Susan.

05:06.567 --> 05:08.438
Better than Susan.

05:10.701 --> 05:13.356
Okay?

05:13.400 --> 05:15.097
I'm gonna take a shower.

05:25.063 --> 05:27.849
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

05:32.244 --> 05:35.378
[ MUSIC PLAYS FROM RADIO ]

05:50.001 --> 05:52.047
♪ Baby we could read all day

05:52.090 --> 05:54.745
♪ And listen as our hearts grow full ♪

05:54.789 --> 06:00.316
♪ No distraction
no more delay ♪

06:00.360 --> 06:02.840
♪ In our minds we travel far

06:02.884 --> 06:05.408
[ PAN SIZZLING ]Mm!

06:05.452 --> 06:10.587
♪ Baby with you is where
I wanna stay ♪

06:10.631 --> 06:12.241
Spearfishing?

06:12.284 --> 06:15.157
Uh, search and rescue operation?
Lost spoon.

06:15.200 --> 06:18.508
Eh, just leave it.

06:18.552 --> 06:22.512
Uh-oh.

06:22.556 --> 06:25.210
Yeah, I know, and it's the
last bottle.

06:25.254 --> 06:27.430
Not for us, it isn't.

06:27.474 --> 06:30.172
15 minutes left on the meatloaf.

06:33.131 --> 06:34.655
Yep, so, I'll be back in ten.

06:34.698 --> 06:36.265
It's okay, Charlie, really.

06:36.308 --> 06:39.834
Hey, an anniversary dinner might
not need to be...

06:39.877 --> 06:42.793
on your anniversary, but it does
need a bottle of fine wine...

06:42.837 --> 06:44.839
for a fine woman.

06:44.882 --> 06:47.494
Huh?

06:47.537 --> 06:51.193
I'll be back before you can say,
"spoon soup."

06:56.416 --> 06:58.505
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

07:01.595 --> 07:04.075
Oh, Mary, don't you look lovely.

07:04.119 --> 07:05.468
[MARY]
What are you doing here?

07:05.512 --> 07:06.730
There you are.

07:08.036 --> 07:09.646
Hey, babe.

07:09.690 --> 07:11.039
Look who I ran into
at the store.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.435
We were grabbing some wine
for dinner and I saw Charlie...

07:15.478 --> 07:18.089
and I thought, why not share
both?

07:18.133 --> 07:22.180
Just the two of us? Yeah, they were... insistent.

07:26.315 --> 07:28.491
Ooh, one bottle of wine
for each of us?

07:28.535 --> 07:31.363
I smell some lowered
inhibitions.

07:34.802 --> 07:36.891
It's... it's... unbelievable.

07:36.934 --> 07:40.503
I mean, that's... that's two
wrecks in two weeks.

07:40.547 --> 07:44.507
So, anyway, her car's in the
shop first and until then...

07:44.551 --> 07:47.031
my car's hers.

07:47.075 --> 07:48.642
Wow, that's rough.

07:48.685 --> 07:52.167
Can you guys imagine me
driving Charlie's truck?

07:52.210 --> 07:54.125
No.[ LAUGHING ]

07:57.694 --> 08:02.525
Oh... what an interesting
reading choice, Mary.

08:02.569 --> 08:05.528
Well, I hand the classics to the
kids all day so I figured...

08:05.572 --> 08:08.488
I would give myself a refresher,
too.

08:08.531 --> 08:11.360
You have high school girls
reading Kate Chopin?

08:11.403 --> 08:13.231
Charlie, do you know what your
wife is reading about?

08:13.275 --> 08:15.712
Can't say I do.

08:15.756 --> 08:17.758
Well, you must have had a hard
time getting married then.

08:20.804 --> 08:24.199
If you can't say, "I do"?

08:24.242 --> 08:26.810
Ah.

08:26.854 --> 08:29.291
I'm just... not much
of a reader.

08:29.334 --> 08:31.554
How can you say that,
you don't read?

08:31.598 --> 08:33.424
I just... I don't really see
the point.

08:33.469 --> 08:34.818
Just for me.

08:34.861 --> 08:36.864
The point is to broaden
your horizons...

08:36.907 --> 08:39.256
you know, escape your life
for a little bit.

08:39.301 --> 08:42.477
Right? I mean... that's... that's
why I read, and write.

08:42.522 --> 08:45.394
Well, I like my life.

08:45.437 --> 08:47.570
So, why would I want
to escape it?

08:47.614 --> 08:50.486
Mary, you get what I'm saying,
right?

08:50.530 --> 08:53.533
I'm not much of a reader,
either.

08:53.576 --> 08:57.188
You're a lawyer. You read.

08:57.232 --> 09:00.322
Mostly traffic citations
and wine labels.

09:00.365 --> 09:01.845
Great year.

09:04.065 --> 09:06.371
Here, to being together.

09:06.415 --> 09:08.417
Come on.

09:12.377 --> 09:14.728
[SUSAN] God knows we've all had
too many lonely nights lately.

09:14.771 --> 09:19.080
Mm. Susan has been having
an affair...

09:19.123 --> 09:20.603
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:20.647 --> 09:23.171
...with her work.

09:23.214 --> 09:27.044
Yeah, so, the last few nights,
I've been home alone...

09:27.088 --> 09:30.831
with no car, no company.

09:30.874 --> 09:32.659
At least you have your reading. And writing.

09:32.702 --> 09:34.530
Yeah. So, Susan?

09:34.574 --> 09:37.402
Were you working last night,
too?

09:37.446 --> 09:39.840
Really hard case.

09:44.322 --> 09:46.716
[TREVOR]
Thank you, guys, it was lovely.

09:46.760 --> 09:49.284
Are you sure you don't want
to kill it off, Mary?

09:49.327 --> 09:51.155
Oh, I couldn't. You guys enjoy.

09:51.199 --> 09:53.984
No, I insist.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.551
Goodnight.

09:55.595 --> 09:58.206
Oh, by the way,
I need my car tomorrow.

09:58.249 --> 09:59.555
So...

09:59.599 --> 10:02.645
You and Susan had dinner
last night?

10:02.689 --> 10:04.560
No.

10:04.604 --> 10:07.302
So...

10:09.696 --> 10:11.611
I got pissed.

10:11.654 --> 10:15.963
So, I threw it in the trash
and then I felt stupid, so...

10:16.006 --> 10:17.660
You lied.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.620
[ SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING ]

10:34.068 --> 10:36.505
[ BRUSHING TEETH ]

10:39.726 --> 10:42.337
[ MUSIC FADES UP ]

10:51.085 --> 10:52.216
Charlie?

11:00.790 --> 11:03.706
I'm really sorry I lied to you.

11:03.750 --> 11:10.191
It was really stupid
and I feel... stupid.

11:10.234 --> 11:12.454
Forgiven.

11:17.154 --> 11:20.244
You got... You, too.

11:20.288 --> 11:21.724
Has that been there
the whole time?

11:21.768 --> 11:23.508
Yeah.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.559
[ GIGGLING ]

11:39.176 --> 11:41.265
[ BELL RINGING ]

11:41.309 --> 11:43.006
[MARY] Oh, make sure you pay
attention to the beginning.

11:43.050 --> 11:45.443
There's a lot of hidden clues
in there.

11:51.058 --> 11:52.668
So you must be in Ms. Keegan's
class.

11:52.712 --> 11:55.279
No, ma'am, just curious.

11:55.323 --> 11:57.499
Enjoy.

12:02.809 --> 12:06.073
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

12:17.824 --> 12:20.783
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

12:25.527 --> 12:26.963
Hey.

12:27.007 --> 12:30.010
Who is that?

12:30.053 --> 12:32.447
My neighbor.

12:32.490 --> 12:34.275
Did he say something to you?

12:34.318 --> 12:37.582
No, was just curious.

12:37.626 --> 12:39.715
He's cute.

12:39.759 --> 12:41.499
Are you hungry?

12:44.851 --> 12:47.418
He's married, Crystal.

12:47.462 --> 12:49.551
But what are you doing here?

12:49.594 --> 12:51.596
I, uh... just thought we should
catch up.

12:51.640 --> 12:54.817
I don't know the last time
I saw you outside of school.

12:54.861 --> 12:56.688
Is Charlie around?

12:56.732 --> 12:58.690
No, he's at the site.

12:58.734 --> 13:00.910
Nice. Have you been out
there lately?

13:00.954 --> 13:02.520
Not much.

13:02.564 --> 13:06.002
You know you can tell me
anything, right?

13:06.046 --> 13:07.525
Are you guys okay?

13:10.833 --> 13:13.705
Yes, everything's fine.

13:13.749 --> 13:17.405
You, uh... you want some tequila?

13:19.015 --> 13:21.191
He's never home anymore.

13:21.235 --> 13:22.540
I mean, he stops in for food
and clothes...

13:22.584 --> 13:24.368
but it's like he's a ghost.

13:24.412 --> 13:26.414
But you know how he is.

13:26.457 --> 13:28.416
He just gets focused
on stuff and...

13:28.459 --> 13:30.897
He missed our anniversary.

13:30.940 --> 13:34.509
I made dinner and everything.

13:34.552 --> 13:38.165
You could've called me,
I would've come over.

13:38.208 --> 13:40.210
If you were alone, I mean.

13:40.254 --> 13:42.082
He told you, didn't he?

13:42.125 --> 13:43.910
Everybody makes mistakes.

13:43.953 --> 13:48.871
That's what... I just can't
help feeling...

13:48.915 --> 13:52.135
like there's something wrong.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.834
Like maybe there's somebody
else.

13:54.877 --> 13:58.663
Are you saying... are you having
an affair?

13:58.707 --> 14:02.885
What? No, I was talking
about Charlie.

14:02.929 --> 14:06.193
I... I'm sorry,
pay no attention to me...

14:06.236 --> 14:08.108
that's the tequila talking.

14:08.151 --> 14:10.371
Mary, you can tell me.

14:10.414 --> 14:13.374
We're just going through
a rough patch.

14:13.417 --> 14:16.377
All couples go through it.
It's perfectly normal.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.292
Right?

14:18.335 --> 14:20.772
I think if your instincts are
telling you something...

14:20.816 --> 14:24.472
isn't right, maybe it's time
you both cleared the air.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.648
You're right, I will.

14:32.523 --> 14:36.310
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

14:36.353 --> 14:38.355
Hey, I was just about to call
you.

14:38.399 --> 14:40.575
[ MUFFLED BREATHING ]

14:40.618 --> 14:42.359
Charlie?

14:42.403 --> 14:44.796
[ MUFFLED BREATHING CONTINUES ]

14:48.148 --> 14:51.194
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

15:07.558 --> 15:10.344
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

15:22.617 --> 15:24.488
Charlie?

15:26.447 --> 15:28.188
[ PHONE CHIMES ]

15:31.017 --> 15:33.454
"I'm sorry." What?

15:33.497 --> 15:36.109
[ PHONE CHIMES ]

15:36.152 --> 15:40.678
[ EERIE MUSIC PLAYING ]

15:40.722 --> 15:46.641
Charlie?

15:46.684 --> 15:50.210
[ CAR ENGINE STARTS ]

15:50.253 --> 15:53.082
[ CAR DRIVES AWAY ]

16:00.829 --> 16:03.005
Charlie, what the hell?

16:08.402 --> 16:12.406
[ PHONE RINGING ]

16:15.191 --> 16:18.020
Charlie?

16:18.064 --> 16:21.284
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

16:24.722 --> 16:26.246
Hey?

16:29.466 --> 16:33.035
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

16:38.040 --> 16:41.087
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP ]

16:55.014 --> 16:57.059
Charlie.

16:57.103 --> 17:01.977
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

17:02.021 --> 17:04.240
[ DISTANT SIRENS APPROACHING ]

17:04.284 --> 17:07.590
Hey... fantastic.

17:07.635 --> 17:10.029
Listen, I'm glad they got
the daughter, but...

17:10.071 --> 17:12.640
they shouldn't have gone
there by themselves.

17:12.683 --> 17:15.817
All right, gotta go.

17:17.297 --> 17:18.602
What are we looking at?

17:18.646 --> 17:20.996
Looks like they fled
around back.

17:21.040 --> 17:25.305
Looks like a single stab wound
to the back.

17:25.348 --> 17:28.134
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

17:35.271 --> 17:36.490
Any sign of a murder weapon?

17:36.533 --> 17:39.058
Not yet.

17:40.450 --> 17:42.104
Where's the wife?

17:42.148 --> 17:43.540
This way.

18:04.474 --> 18:07.303
[ EERIE MUSIC PLAYING ]

18:15.311 --> 18:21.012
Ms. Saunders?
Detective Brady Malone.

18:21.056 --> 18:23.972
Think you'd be able to answer
a few questions for me?

18:38.508 --> 18:42.208
You told Deputy Davies that
you'd gotten a phone call.

18:42.251 --> 18:44.819
What can you tell me about that?

18:44.862 --> 18:48.170
It was from Charlie.

18:48.214 --> 18:51.391
Or at least I think it was.

18:51.434 --> 18:56.004
When I answered, there was
just... breathing.

18:56.047 --> 18:58.659
Breathing? Heavy breathing.

18:58.702 --> 19:00.313
It frightened me.

19:00.356 --> 19:02.750
Did you think the person
breathing could be Charlie?

19:02.793 --> 19:05.970
Maybe.

19:06.014 --> 19:07.842
The reception here is...

19:07.885 --> 19:09.887
Did he sound like he was
in trouble?

19:09.931 --> 19:12.238
I don't know.

19:16.764 --> 19:20.637
You been drinking tonight? No.

19:20.681 --> 19:27.383
Well... I had a drink earlier
with my sister-in-law.

19:27.427 --> 19:29.777
But it was just one.

19:29.820 --> 19:33.824
One and a half... maybe.

19:33.868 --> 19:37.263
I'm sorry.

19:37.306 --> 19:39.917
That's a very unique
wedding band.

19:39.961 --> 19:41.354
Thank you.

19:43.138 --> 19:45.793
My husband had them made for us.

19:45.836 --> 19:49.275
He has one just like it.

19:49.318 --> 19:51.102
Did he wear his everyday?

19:52.669 --> 19:56.847
Yes, of course. Why?

19:56.891 --> 20:00.199
I'm... sure it's nothing.

20:00.242 --> 20:02.026
But right now, he isn't.

20:02.070 --> 20:03.637
What do you mean?

20:03.680 --> 20:06.683
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

20:07.902 --> 20:09.208
He was just old enough...

20:09.251 --> 20:12.254
that I viewed him
as kind of a parent.

20:12.298 --> 20:14.430
Except I didn't have to worry
about him...

20:14.474 --> 20:15.997
telling on me or anything.

20:16.040 --> 20:17.912
It doesn't feel right.

20:17.955 --> 20:22.612
[CRYSTAL] Just be myself and......burying him without it.

20:22.656 --> 20:28.139
My brother was kind...
and he was gentle.

20:28.183 --> 20:32.013
A truly creative soul.

20:32.056 --> 20:39.890
And he was loyal, so loyal,
and this just isn't fair.

20:39.934 --> 20:45.461
Keep watching over me, Charlie,
I still need you.

20:46.984 --> 20:50.466
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC FADES UP ]

20:50.510 --> 20:53.600
I should've talked about the
Little Owl.

20:53.643 --> 20:56.080
His nickname for you?

20:56.124 --> 21:00.041
You know, I met him working
at the dentist office?

21:00.084 --> 21:03.305
Right, right, he, uh...
he knocked his front teeth out.

21:03.349 --> 21:06.569
Construction accident.Yeah.

21:06.613 --> 21:09.659
He didn't have insurance then,
so...

21:09.703 --> 21:12.401
He spent hours just sitting
in the waiting room.

21:12.445 --> 21:15.752
I was in charge of answering
the phones and...

21:15.796 --> 21:18.407
as you can imagine, a lot of
people who call the dentist...

21:18.451 --> 21:22.063
aren't speaking very clearly,
so... he just sat there...

21:22.106 --> 21:25.893
listening to me for hours,
say over and over again&

21:25.936 --> 21:28.765
Who? Who?

21:28.809 --> 21:31.986
That's funny.

21:32.029 --> 21:33.422
And if he's up there...

21:33.466 --> 21:38.645
somewhere listening to my
thoughts.

21:38.688 --> 21:42.083
He's hearing the exact
same thing.

21:42.126 --> 21:44.999
Because I need to know who,
Susan.

21:45.042 --> 21:48.437
Who did this?

21:48.481 --> 21:52.136
I know, Mary, I know.

21:52.180 --> 21:54.225
I'm gonna pay my respects.

21:59.753 --> 22:02.016
Mary... No, Trevor!

22:02.059 --> 22:04.410
I can't stand seeing you
in pain like this.

22:04.453 --> 22:05.889
Please don't push me away,
not now...

22:05.933 --> 22:08.327
Don't make me.

22:08.370 --> 22:11.417
How have you been holding up?

22:11.460 --> 22:15.334
We're all here for you.
Anything you need.

22:15.377 --> 22:16.900
We'll get through this
as a family.

22:16.944 --> 22:18.206
Thank you.

22:20.774 --> 22:22.558
Is Crystal okay?

22:25.387 --> 22:26.910
She will be.

22:26.954 --> 22:30.000
You know how close they were.

22:30.044 --> 22:35.266
Mrs. Saunders, I'm Trevor.
I'm so sorry for you loss.

22:35.310 --> 22:37.181
[TREVOR] Charlie was a very good
friend of mine.

22:37.225 --> 22:39.706
[MRS. SAUNDERS] I don't recall
him mentioning your name.

22:39.749 --> 22:42.926
[TREVOR] Well, he was a social
butterfly...

22:42.970 --> 22:45.712
even if he seemed quiet.

22:45.755 --> 22:49.150
Hm... I guess there's a lot
I didn't know about...

22:49.193 --> 22:50.978
If you'll excuse me?

22:51.021 --> 22:54.155
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

23:01.249 --> 23:04.078
You know, you're lucky
my mother is here.

23:04.121 --> 23:07.081
I would never embarrass
Charlie in front of her!

23:07.124 --> 23:09.736
What do you mean? I saw you.

23:09.779 --> 23:13.130
I know what you did!

23:13.174 --> 23:15.698
He isn't even in the ground
and here you are...

23:15.742 --> 23:17.526
standing next to that guy.

23:17.570 --> 23:20.181
He didn't... Crystal...
we didn't...

23:20.224 --> 23:21.748
What are you talking about?

23:21.791 --> 23:26.883
Did you do it?
Did you... did you kill him?

23:26.927 --> 23:29.190
No! You're lying!

23:29.233 --> 23:31.105
I know you're...

23:34.064 --> 23:39.418
He was a good man, Mary, and he
deserved better than this.

23:39.461 --> 23:41.376
He deserved better than you.

23:41.420 --> 23:46.468
Don't make me do this.
Don't make me tell.

23:50.994 --> 23:53.606
What was that about?

23:53.649 --> 23:55.216
I...

23:55.259 --> 23:58.437
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

24:04.007 --> 24:07.097
I thought after a week,
she might calm down...

24:10.100 --> 24:14.931
but, well... she can be
stubborn.

24:18.544 --> 24:21.198
Does she really think I did it?

24:21.242 --> 24:23.331
I think she just wants
an answer.

24:25.942 --> 24:27.944
Have you heard anything new
from the police?

24:27.988 --> 24:29.163
Nothing.

24:37.345 --> 24:41.262
Crystal's just confused.
She'll come around.

24:41.305 --> 24:44.395
I hope so.

24:44.439 --> 24:46.310
By the way, did you find the...

24:46.354 --> 24:48.138
Oh... oh, yes.

24:48.182 --> 24:50.097
Of course, it's right over here.

25:00.063 --> 25:03.850
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

25:18.386 --> 25:19.866
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

25:21.171 --> 25:23.217
Good morning, Ms. Saunders.

25:23.260 --> 25:27.264
If you don't mind, I'd like to
ask you a few questions.

25:27.308 --> 25:29.179
We were able to recover most
of the information...

25:29.223 --> 25:30.877
on Charlie's cell phone, and...

25:30.920 --> 25:33.749
He wasn't texting someone
named Cassandra, was he?

25:33.793 --> 25:34.924
Cassandra James?

25:34.968 --> 25:36.447
Not that I'm aware of.

25:36.491 --> 25:37.753
Well, because she was at his
funeral...

25:37.797 --> 25:39.538
and I went to her website...

25:39.581 --> 25:45.195
Mary... now trust me, we are
exploring every possibility.

25:45.239 --> 25:48.329
Now, his last two text messages
to you...

25:48.372 --> 25:50.244
I'm sorry, please don't be mad.

25:50.287 --> 25:52.333
Yeah.

25:52.376 --> 25:54.596
But he couldn't have sent those.

25:54.640 --> 25:57.643
I didn't receive them
until after he was...

25:57.686 --> 26:01.734
Well, it turns out, they were
sent several minutes...

26:01.777 --> 26:05.607
before you received them...
bad reception.

26:05.651 --> 26:09.176
If it was Charlie, do you
have any idea...

26:09.219 --> 26:11.178
what they could've been
in reference to?

26:11.221 --> 26:12.962
Did you fight that day?

26:13.006 --> 26:14.442
Have a disagreement of any
kind...

26:14.485 --> 26:15.748
that he might need
to apologize for?

26:15.791 --> 26:17.619
No.

26:17.663 --> 26:20.230
You and Charlie having
difficulties?

26:20.274 --> 26:21.536
Difficulties?

26:21.580 --> 26:23.364
In your marriage.

26:23.407 --> 26:25.714
No, why would...

26:25.758 --> 26:32.112
Just... well, him not wearing
his wedding band and all.

26:32.155 --> 26:33.722
You know, maybe it'd be better
if we can go inside and talk.

26:33.766 --> 26:35.419
You got a warrant?

26:37.421 --> 26:38.640
Well?

26:38.684 --> 26:41.208
Just exploring every
possibility.

26:41.251 --> 26:42.992
Yeah, maybe you should possibly
start by finding...

26:43.036 --> 26:45.560
the murder weapon instead
of torturing the mourning widow?

26:48.084 --> 26:49.564
I'll be in touch.

26:51.435 --> 26:52.828
Okay, thanks.

26:56.049 --> 26:58.704
Steak, a good cut.

26:58.747 --> 27:01.271
My lasagna didn't kill you,
neither will this.

27:01.315 --> 27:02.969
Thank you.

27:04.927 --> 27:07.364
Has he been asking a lot
of questions like that?

27:07.408 --> 27:09.628
Mm-hm.

27:09.671 --> 27:11.891
Mind if I come in? Yeah.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.335
I'm not really hungry.

27:21.378 --> 27:24.207
You look like the walking dead.

27:30.692 --> 27:32.868
Eat it.

27:32.912 --> 27:35.610
I guess I haven't done the best
job of taking care of myself.

27:35.654 --> 27:38.091
Well, that ends starting today.

27:38.134 --> 27:39.658
And also, I don't want you
talking to anyone...

27:39.701 --> 27:41.007
without a lawyer.

27:41.050 --> 27:42.443
If he calls you, come get me.

27:42.486 --> 27:44.532
Susan, you do traffic law.

27:44.575 --> 27:46.708
I'm a criminal defense attorney,
and yes...

27:46.752 --> 27:50.581
that includes contesting
violations and citations...

27:50.625 --> 27:54.063
Mary... let me help you.

27:54.107 --> 27:57.240
I know that they seem like
harmless questions.

27:57.284 --> 27:59.721
You're a suspect.

27:59.765 --> 28:01.592
But I found Charlie!

28:01.636 --> 28:03.769
I'm the one who called
the police!

28:03.812 --> 28:07.120
Most murders are committed by a
spouse or a significant other.

28:07.163 --> 28:09.252
The police know this.

28:09.296 --> 28:11.559
You've been in their crosshairs
since day one.

28:11.602 --> 28:13.474
What am I supposed to do?

28:13.517 --> 28:16.042
Whatever it is you normally do.

28:17.913 --> 28:19.480
Well, there was this woman
at the funeral...

28:19.523 --> 28:20.786
I've never seen before.

28:20.829 --> 28:22.048
Maybe I could find out...

28:22.091 --> 28:24.877
No, Mary, whatever you
normally do.

28:24.920 --> 28:28.358
The only way to deal with death
is by living life.

28:33.233 --> 28:36.540
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

28:37.803 --> 28:39.979
[ BELL RINGING ]

28:42.721 --> 28:44.766
[ HORN HONKING ]Mary!

28:44.810 --> 28:48.335
Oh, uh... hi. Oh, you poor thing.
How are you?

28:48.378 --> 28:52.905
Uh... hi, Lizzy, I'm just taking
it day by day.

28:52.948 --> 28:55.342
Well, I just want you to know
that we're all behind you.

28:55.385 --> 28:57.213
Thank you.

28:57.257 --> 28:58.737
And don't you pay any mind
to what people are saying...

28:58.780 --> 29:00.042
about you, okay?

29:01.609 --> 29:02.697
Okay.

29:12.315 --> 29:15.362
Mary... didn't expect to see you
back so soon.

29:15.405 --> 29:18.713
Do you have a minute? Sure, of course.

29:22.325 --> 29:23.979
I was hoping to talk to you...

29:24.023 --> 29:26.765
about scheduling my return
to work.

29:26.808 --> 29:28.767
Well, when were you thinking?

29:28.810 --> 29:29.811
I was thinking tomorrow?

29:34.076 --> 29:36.513
Look, there's no need to rush
back.

29:36.557 --> 29:38.689
You've been through a terrible
ordeal.

29:38.733 --> 29:41.736
We all understand.

29:41.780 --> 29:44.652
If you need more time to grieve,
I want you to take it.

29:44.695 --> 29:47.002
What I need is to get back
to work.

29:47.046 --> 29:49.744
I can't be in that house
alone anymore.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.354
It's too hard.

29:52.747 --> 29:56.403
Okay... we'll make it happen.

29:56.446 --> 29:57.839
Thank you.

30:00.799 --> 30:05.020
Uh... if it gets too much,
you'll let me know. Okay?

30:10.069 --> 30:12.811
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

30:33.440 --> 30:37.139
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

30:42.449 --> 30:44.625
[ DOOR OPENS ][ GASPS ]

30:49.760 --> 30:50.936
I missed you.

30:53.373 --> 30:55.070
[CASSANDRA] Who do you want? You.

30:56.332 --> 30:57.464
Who?

30:57.507 --> 30:58.944
Only you.

31:01.250 --> 31:04.775
[ OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING ]

31:28.930 --> 31:31.890
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]DR]

31:45.033 --> 31:47.688
[ CALL RINGING ]

31:47.731 --> 31:49.559
[WOMAN OVER PHONE]
Good afternoon...

31:49.603 --> 31:51.735
Screws and Bolts Hardware,
how may I help today?

31:51.779 --> 31:55.652
Yes... is this Cassandra James?

31:55.696 --> 31:56.958
[WOMAN OVER PHONE] No ma'am, she's not in today...

31:57.002 --> 31:58.960
but if you're looking for tools...

31:59.004 --> 32:01.832
Uh... do you know when she's
gonna be back?

32:01.876 --> 32:03.095
[WOMAN OVER PHONE] Not for a while, I'm afraid.

32:03.138 --> 32:07.360
Oh, really... why?

32:07.403 --> 32:08.839
[WOMAN OVER PHONE]
She had a bunch of vacation...

32:08.883 --> 32:11.364
time saved up, cashed it in all last week.

32:11.407 --> 32:14.236
I guess sometimes you just have to get away from it all.

32:14.280 --> 32:17.196
Yeah, I guess so.

32:17.239 --> 32:20.590
You know people at the DMV,
right?

32:20.634 --> 32:24.768
So you can get information on
people, like... like addresses?

32:24.812 --> 32:26.727
I might know a guy.

32:26.770 --> 32:29.164
Why do you want this
girl's address?

32:29.208 --> 32:32.341
I think Charlie was having
an affair.

32:32.385 --> 32:34.909
Really?

32:37.129 --> 32:40.262
I'm not sure.
I don't have proof.

32:42.047 --> 32:43.265
But there were signs.

32:43.309 --> 32:46.573
What do you mean? He was distant.

32:46.616 --> 32:49.489
And I know he was busy at work,
but...

32:49.532 --> 32:52.622
It felt like he was keeping
something from me.

32:52.666 --> 32:56.017
Do you have anything concrete?
Did you see anything?

32:56.061 --> 33:01.196
The night before he died,
he came home with scratches...

33:01.240 --> 33:05.026
on his back and they looked
like they were... you know.

33:05.070 --> 33:06.810
Did you tell the police this?

33:06.854 --> 33:09.509
No.

33:09.552 --> 33:12.599
I mean, it looks bad, right?

33:12.642 --> 33:14.035
I think my husband is having
an affair...

33:14.079 --> 33:15.254
and then he winds up dead?

33:15.297 --> 33:17.517
Well, it doesn't look good.

33:19.736 --> 33:24.785
You think that thisgirl and
Charlie were having an affair?

33:24.828 --> 33:28.919
This is Cassandra James.
I first saw her at the funeral.

33:28.963 --> 33:31.270
No one knew who she was
and when she saw me...

33:31.313 --> 33:33.663
she ran away before I could
talk to her.

33:33.707 --> 33:35.578
So, I had to do a little
research and I found out...

33:35.622 --> 33:38.407
that she worked at the hardware
store that Charlie went to.

33:38.451 --> 33:41.280
I mean, this girl is half
our age.

33:41.323 --> 33:46.111
If she was Charlie's mistress,
do you really wanna know now?

33:46.154 --> 33:50.332
If this girl was seeing Charlie
at the beach house...

33:50.376 --> 33:53.988
she could be our best lead
in finding out who killed him.

33:55.903 --> 33:56.860
Do you really think that she
would tell you...

33:56.904 --> 33:58.514
if something's going on?

33:58.558 --> 34:01.039
Trust me, Susan, I'll be able
to tell.

34:03.215 --> 34:05.608
And you said that the police
think I'm a suspect.

34:05.652 --> 34:08.393
Maybe it's time we give
'em another one.

34:17.925 --> 34:19.753
All right, well, you better
not start...

34:19.795 --> 34:21.101
going through old yearbooks
next.

34:21.146 --> 34:22.364
I'm only doing this once.

34:25.150 --> 34:30.329
Daryl, hi, yeah, it's Susan.

34:30.371 --> 34:31.938
Can you run a plate for me?

34:31.982 --> 34:35.072
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

34:35.116 --> 34:37.813
Okay, thanks, Daryl.

34:43.168 --> 34:45.300
I really should be going
with you.

34:45.344 --> 34:47.128
I'll be okay.

34:47.172 --> 34:48.998
Be careful.

34:49.043 --> 34:51.001
And if you find out anything,
anything at all.

34:51.045 --> 34:52.525
Promise that you'll tell me.

34:52.568 --> 34:54.440
I will.

34:58.052 --> 35:01.142
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

35:15.765 --> 35:18.028
Hi, excuse me, do you know, um...

35:25.993 --> 35:27.473
Oh...

35:29.083 --> 35:31.520
Can I help you? Hi.

35:31.564 --> 35:34.958
Cassandra, um... you don't
know me.

35:35.002 --> 35:38.179
I'm Charlie Saunder's wife.

35:38.223 --> 35:40.747
I saw you at Charlie's funeral.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.618
How did you know my husband?

35:42.662 --> 35:44.751
I work at Screws and Bolts.

35:44.794 --> 35:46.622
Charlie came in a lot while
he was working...

35:46.666 --> 35:48.407
at the house on the beach.

35:48.450 --> 35:49.843
He told you about the beach
house?

35:49.886 --> 35:51.540
Sure.

35:51.584 --> 35:53.499
Did he take you there?

35:53.542 --> 35:56.197
I wouldn't be any use onsite,
I just work at the counter.

35:56.241 --> 35:58.808
I'm asking if he took you
there socially.

35:58.852 --> 36:00.984
How close were you to my
husband?

36:01.028 --> 36:04.771
I told you, he was a customer
I knew and I liked.

36:04.814 --> 36:06.642
Sounds like he was more
than that.

36:06.686 --> 36:08.470
He dies and all of a sudden...

36:08.514 --> 36:10.994
you have to go on extended leave
from work?

36:11.038 --> 36:12.735
That doesn't sound like
just a customer.

36:12.779 --> 36:15.173
[MAN]
Cass, where's my wallet?

36:15.216 --> 36:17.349
Just a second.

36:17.392 --> 36:20.265
Look, the only thing going on
between your husband and me...

36:20.308 --> 36:22.615
was a display case of drill
bits, okay?

36:25.748 --> 36:29.839
I'm sorry, I didn't realize you
had a... boyfriend.

36:29.883 --> 36:33.278
I have a husband and a honeymoon
to get packed for, so...

36:33.321 --> 36:35.889
I guess I misread the situation.

36:35.932 --> 36:39.371
You're wrong about Charlie.
He never hit on me.

36:39.414 --> 36:41.329
Not like the other customers.

36:41.373 --> 36:43.679
[MAN]
Jesus, Cass.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.682
You had yourself a winner.
Sorry.

36:49.207 --> 36:52.253
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

37:05.135 --> 37:08.487
Sorry. I didn't mean
to scare you.

37:08.530 --> 37:10.532
How did you get in here?

37:10.576 --> 37:12.317
Did he make this for you?

37:12.360 --> 37:14.275
Trevor?

37:14.319 --> 37:18.018
His "owl"... that's what he used
to call you, right?

37:18.061 --> 37:20.194
Why is that?

37:21.717 --> 37:24.590
Did you used to keep him
up all night?

37:24.633 --> 37:26.156
What do you want?

37:26.200 --> 37:28.071
I left messages.

37:28.115 --> 37:29.682
I've been busy.

37:32.337 --> 37:33.860
Why are you so mad at me?

37:33.903 --> 37:37.777
Because I asked you to give me
space.

37:37.820 --> 37:39.605
And here you are in my house.

37:42.477 --> 37:44.827
You're in pain.

37:44.871 --> 37:49.223
I get it, but pushing people
away is not the answer.

37:49.267 --> 37:50.833
I wanna be here for you.

37:50.877 --> 37:53.706
You can't be. I have to be.

37:55.969 --> 37:59.625
Mary, we're... we're friends.
I care for you.

37:59.668 --> 38:03.324
I... I haven't shown it.

38:03.368 --> 38:07.546
No! You've shown it.

38:07.589 --> 38:11.637
And now my memory of his final
days will always be...

38:11.680 --> 38:14.379
You're just as guilty as I am.

38:14.422 --> 38:16.250
You kissed me back, Mary.

38:16.294 --> 38:18.383
You should go.

38:21.647 --> 38:23.257
Why?

38:26.478 --> 38:30.308
Because you're not Charlie,
and you never will be.

38:30.351 --> 38:32.614
Exactly!

38:32.658 --> 38:35.095
Get out of my house, Trevor.

38:39.882 --> 38:41.710
You need time.

38:41.754 --> 38:43.886
I understand, I do.

38:47.455 --> 38:52.112
Just, Mary... he's gone.

38:54.723 --> 38:57.944
But he was gone a long time
before that.

38:59.249 --> 39:01.382
I was there for you.

39:01.426 --> 39:03.079
Still am.

39:05.168 --> 39:08.476
Just... just don't lose what
you've still got.

39:18.704 --> 39:22.142
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

39:48.777 --> 39:50.431
[ VASE SMASHING ]

39:56.481 --> 39:59.788
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

40:31.298 --> 40:33.126
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

40:43.528 --> 40:44.572
Any other signs of foul play?

40:47.662 --> 40:49.447
I... I... I don't think so.

40:49.490 --> 40:52.232
I don't know, not that
I can really see.

40:53.538 --> 40:55.365
You leave that window open?

40:55.409 --> 40:57.324
I don't know. I don't...
I don't remember.

40:57.367 --> 40:59.282
You better have a warrant!

40:59.326 --> 41:01.459
You have absolutely no right to
be inside of this house tonight!

41:03.025 --> 41:04.244
What's going on?

41:04.287 --> 41:06.289
Somebody was in my house.

41:06.333 --> 41:08.596
I'm okay, I'm just a little
freaked out.

41:08.640 --> 41:09.858
If you like, I can arrange
for a hotel...

41:09.902 --> 41:11.556
if you don't feel comfortable
here.

41:11.599 --> 41:14.254
No, you're staying with us. I... I couldn't.

41:14.297 --> 41:16.343
No, he's right, you shouldn't
be here alone.

41:16.386 --> 41:18.824
And Trevor's tied up writing,
it'll just be the two of us.

41:23.437 --> 41:25.178
This is great.

41:27.093 --> 41:28.921
Are you sure this is all right?

41:28.964 --> 41:30.923
And that Trevor won't mind?

41:30.966 --> 41:34.274
Well, he's not here,
so he's not allowed to mind.

41:34.317 --> 41:36.842
Where is he, by the way?

41:36.885 --> 41:39.845
Who knows where he goes.
Coffee shops, bars.

41:39.888 --> 41:41.934
Hard to say.

41:41.977 --> 41:45.372
He's been spending a lot of late
nights just writing away.

41:45.415 --> 41:47.853
I'd give him a hard time,
but that'd be hypocritical.

41:50.116 --> 41:51.552
You okay?

41:51.596 --> 41:55.208
Yeah.

41:55.251 --> 41:56.557
Just been a long day.

41:56.601 --> 41:59.604
Well, relax, you're with friends
now.

41:59.647 --> 42:03.999
Have some wine, take a hot
shower and get some sleep.

42:04.043 --> 42:06.872
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

42:16.490 --> 42:19.667
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ][ SHOWER RUNNING ]

42:50.263 --> 42:52.004
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

43:02.536 --> 43:06.148
[ EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES ]

43:23.296 --> 43:25.646
What's gotten into you?

43:29.476 --> 43:31.304
Wait, stop.

43:34.916 --> 43:37.266
Much better.

43:59.941 --> 44:01.421
Hi.

44:01.464 --> 44:04.685
Good morning. I heard we had
a house guest.

44:04.729 --> 44:07.470
Yeah, I had some trouble
last night.

44:07.514 --> 44:10.996
Well, like I said,
you can count on me.

44:11.039 --> 44:12.432
On us.

44:12.475 --> 44:15.435
You feeling better? Yes.

44:15.478 --> 44:17.350
Thanks again for everything.

44:17.393 --> 44:19.308
Well, the bed is yours
for as long as you want it.

44:19.352 --> 44:21.310
Right, Trevor? Of course.

44:23.704 --> 44:26.141
I appreciate that.

44:26.185 --> 44:29.971
I'm gonna get going.
I'm gonna be late for work.

44:32.060 --> 44:33.932
Returning.

44:33.975 --> 44:35.934
Oh, this is a good one.
Did you enjoy it?

44:35.977 --> 44:37.675
Very much. Okay, you're all set.

44:37.718 --> 44:39.111
Thank you.

44:39.154 --> 44:42.114
Did you kill your husband?

44:46.335 --> 44:48.250
You're all set.

44:51.732 --> 44:55.127
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

45:02.525 --> 45:04.310
Crystal?

45:04.353 --> 45:06.878
Got a lot of nerve showing
your face here.

45:06.921 --> 45:09.402
What are you telling people? Telling people?

45:09.445 --> 45:12.971
I haven't been telling people
anything.

45:13.014 --> 45:15.234
They see you hiding behind
your lawyer friend.

45:15.277 --> 45:17.410
It's sick.

45:17.453 --> 45:21.457
The wife of the guy who... Who what, Crystal?

45:21.501 --> 45:24.896
You know me. You have known
me for years.

45:24.939 --> 45:26.767
Do you really think I'm capable
of murder?

45:26.811 --> 45:28.595
I thought I knew you.

45:28.638 --> 45:30.815
Listen, can we just go talk
about this somewhere?

45:30.858 --> 45:32.512
You can ask me any questions
you have.

45:33.992 --> 45:36.037
You know, I loved him, too.

45:36.081 --> 45:38.213
Will your lawyer friend
be there?

45:38.257 --> 45:40.476
Just you and me.

45:40.520 --> 45:42.827
All right.

45:42.870 --> 45:46.047
[ EERIE MUSIC PLAYING ]

45:53.272 --> 45:56.014
[ INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER ]

45:59.974 --> 46:02.585
Did you find something?

46:02.629 --> 46:08.069
No. Just have a few questions
for Mrs.... for Ms. Saunders.

46:08.113 --> 46:10.985
Well, I will leave you to it
then.

46:11.029 --> 46:16.382
No, no! This won't take long.
Right?

46:16.425 --> 46:20.603
Well, that depends on you.
Care to step inside.

46:20.647 --> 46:23.737
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

46:26.044 --> 46:28.829
You sure you don't want
your lawyer here?

46:32.354 --> 46:34.487
No, I'm fine.

46:36.663 --> 46:39.100
But, like she said,
why are you here...

46:39.144 --> 46:41.581
and not out searching for
a suspect or the murder weapon?

46:43.017 --> 46:45.759
Funny you mention that.

46:52.635 --> 46:57.292
Found that at the scene.
It was in a shed out back.

46:57.336 --> 47:00.469
Look familiar?

47:00.513 --> 47:03.559
At Screws and Bolts they sell
all kinds of hunting...

47:06.824 --> 47:09.565
Found traces of dried blood
on the blade.

47:09.609 --> 47:12.830
Lab results came back as
a match for Charlie's DNA.

47:12.873 --> 47:17.356
Oh... okay.

47:17.399 --> 47:19.184
So, maybe test it
for fingerprints.

47:19.227 --> 47:21.708
We did, and we found yours.

47:23.231 --> 47:25.320
That's impossible.

47:25.364 --> 47:27.366
You have to believe me, I...

47:32.675 --> 47:35.069
I think I need my lawyer.

47:35.113 --> 47:37.593
[ MUSIC FADES UP ]

47:43.034 --> 47:44.862
Can I have a glass of water??

47:46.907 --> 47:49.301
They didn't give you one
at the station?

47:49.344 --> 47:51.390
Actually, do you have any wine?

48:05.883 --> 48:07.667
Mary...

48:07.710 --> 48:11.236
if I'm going to help you,
I need you to listen to me.

48:11.279 --> 48:13.978
I told you not to talk to them
without representation.

48:14.021 --> 48:17.372
I didn't know about the knife.

48:17.416 --> 48:19.897
I'm just telling the truth.

48:19.940 --> 48:22.029
Well, right now the truth
could be the worst thing...

48:22.073 --> 48:25.076
that you could tell them. What do you mean?

48:25.119 --> 48:28.035
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

48:32.083 --> 48:34.520
I need you to be honest with me.

48:34.563 --> 48:36.087
I have been.

48:36.130 --> 48:37.915
Look...

48:37.958 --> 48:39.655
your marriage was on the rocks.
Maybe you thought...

48:39.699 --> 48:41.614
that he was cheating on you. Susan?

48:41.657 --> 48:44.138
And sometimes people do things
in the heat of the moment...

48:44.182 --> 48:46.532
and if they blindside us with
information like that...

48:46.575 --> 48:49.839
and I don't know it,
I can't protect you.

48:49.883 --> 48:51.624
So, if there's something
that you're not telling me...

48:51.667 --> 48:53.191
I need to know. Now.

48:54.975 --> 48:56.542
I didn't kill Charlie.

48:58.587 --> 49:00.938
I didn't!

49:03.418 --> 49:04.942
But you thought that he was
cheating on you?

49:04.985 --> 49:06.291
No!

49:07.118 --> 49:08.336
No.

49:09.511 --> 49:11.774
He wasn't.

49:12.645 --> 49:14.560
Okay.

49:15.865 --> 49:17.650
Let's talk about knives.

49:20.696 --> 49:23.134
What about traffic cams?

49:23.177 --> 49:24.657
What about them?

49:24.700 --> 49:26.485
Are there any near
the beach house?

49:26.528 --> 49:28.530
Like maybe near the crossroads?

49:28.574 --> 49:30.228
Huh.

49:30.271 --> 49:33.666
Why didn't I think of that?
I'll look into it.

49:33.709 --> 49:36.625
How many times did you go
to the beach house?

49:36.669 --> 49:38.018
A few.

49:38.062 --> 49:40.151
Did you ever bring Charlie
dinner there?

49:40.194 --> 49:42.718
Like, maybe a steak and you left
a knife there afterwards?

49:42.762 --> 49:44.024
Maybe you did.

49:44.068 --> 49:45.417
No one will buy that.

49:45.460 --> 49:47.114
They'll buy whatever
I sell them.

49:47.158 --> 49:49.769
I'm persuasive.

49:49.812 --> 49:52.032
What if the person who
broke into my house...

49:52.076 --> 49:55.035
stole the steak knife and then
planted it at the crime scene?

49:55.079 --> 49:58.778
If that's the case,
then where's the real weapon?

49:58.821 --> 50:01.737
And what motive would somebody
possibly have for doing that?

50:01.781 --> 50:03.043
[ DOOR OPENS ]

50:03.087 --> 50:05.350
Oh, you're home early.

50:05.393 --> 50:08.222
Got a lot done. I was just
anxious to get home.

50:11.965 --> 50:13.445
Hope I'm not interrupting
anything.

50:13.488 --> 50:15.534
Nope. Grab a plate and join us.

50:15.577 --> 50:16.796
That looks great.

50:16.839 --> 50:19.712
Any news on Charlie?

50:19.755 --> 50:21.801
No... it's just crazy.

50:21.844 --> 50:26.023
I can't imagine how anybody
would think that you did it.

50:26.066 --> 50:28.808
What is wrong with the world?

50:30.549 --> 50:32.855
I think I'm gonna go to bed.

50:32.899 --> 50:34.335
Really?

50:34.379 --> 50:36.816
Yeah. I'll see you
in the morning.

50:39.471 --> 50:42.909
[ MUSIC PLAYING ]

50:42.952 --> 50:45.042
What's that about?

50:45.085 --> 50:47.087
I have no idea.

50:53.572 --> 50:55.008
Those are cute.

50:57.141 --> 50:58.533
You scared me.

50:58.577 --> 51:00.318
I didn't mean to.

51:00.361 --> 51:02.798
I just came to see
if you wanted anything.

51:02.842 --> 51:06.280
If there was anything
I could do for you.

51:07.586 --> 51:10.502
Nope. I'm good.

51:12.112 --> 51:15.028
You seem a little tense is all.

51:15.072 --> 51:16.986
I mean, what kind of host would
I be, if I didn't...

51:17.030 --> 51:18.901
make sure all your needs
were met?

51:22.253 --> 51:25.560
Well, if you change your mind.

51:34.395 --> 51:35.570
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

51:35.614 --> 51:37.572
Come in.

51:39.400 --> 51:41.098
You wanted to see me?

51:41.141 --> 51:42.403
Yes, uh...

51:42.447 --> 51:44.275
can I talk to you for a moment?

51:44.318 --> 51:45.928
Sure.

51:52.021 --> 51:54.415
Is everything okay?

51:54.459 --> 51:56.200
Look, I know you want
to get back...

51:56.243 --> 51:59.290
to your familiar schedule,
but I'm just not sure...

51:59.333 --> 52:03.337
it's the right thing, after all.

52:03.381 --> 52:06.471
I don't understand,
where's this coming from?

52:06.514 --> 52:11.780
Well, there have been some
complaints from parents...

52:11.824 --> 52:14.479
concerned of the influence
your situation...

52:14.522 --> 52:16.655
may have on the students.

52:16.698 --> 52:18.483
My situation?

52:18.526 --> 52:20.963
The, uh...

52:21.007 --> 52:25.316
events surrounding
your husband's death.

52:25.359 --> 52:29.363
It's Crystal, she's just upset
about the whole thing...

52:29.407 --> 52:32.714
we all are, but she's
just confused.

52:32.758 --> 52:36.283
I also know the police have
questioned you and, uh...

52:36.327 --> 52:39.199
well, I'm afraid I'm gonna
have to place...

52:39.243 --> 52:41.984
you on indefinite leave.

52:42.028 --> 52:43.682
Please, no.

52:43.725 --> 52:46.685
Look, I'm sorry, Mary,
but my hands are tied.

52:46.728 --> 52:49.166
I have lost everything,
I cannot lose this, too.

52:50.254 --> 52:51.907
Look, there's uh...

52:51.951 --> 52:54.997
a schoolboard meeting tonight.

52:55.041 --> 52:56.956
If you like, why don't
you stop by?

52:56.999 --> 52:59.654
It'll give you some time
to plead your case.

52:59.698 --> 53:01.439
Thank you.

53:01.482 --> 53:05.312
Now, uh... if you don't mind.

53:05.356 --> 53:07.096
I'll uh...

53:07.140 --> 53:08.663
walk you to the parking lot.

53:13.320 --> 53:14.669
[ SIGHS ]

53:15.627 --> 53:16.845
[ HORN HONKS ]

53:18.891 --> 53:21.415
It's an issue.
All I'm saying is...

53:21.459 --> 53:23.722
we gotta crack down
on security here.

53:27.073 --> 53:29.162
I'm so glad you're here.

53:29.206 --> 53:31.295
I want you to know,
I signed that petition...

53:31.338 --> 53:33.427
but only under duress.

53:33.471 --> 53:35.777
Petition?

53:35.821 --> 53:37.170
Yeah.

53:37.214 --> 53:39.085
The one to get you fired.

53:39.128 --> 53:41.305
[PRINCIPAL JONES] I'll take
that under consideration.

53:41.348 --> 53:44.177
All right then, at this time,
I'd like to offer the floor...

53:44.221 --> 53:46.092
to Mary Saunders.

53:51.445 --> 53:54.361
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

53:56.668 --> 53:58.365
[ DOOR OPENS ]

54:06.852 --> 54:09.202
First of all, I would like
to thank all of you...

54:09.246 --> 54:12.771
for giving me the chance
to address you directly.

54:12.814 --> 54:17.471
I know there have been
a lot of questions.

54:17.515 --> 54:20.648
This morning I learned
that I was suspended...

54:20.692 --> 54:23.608
from my position
as school librarian.

54:23.651 --> 54:26.785
That some of you may...

54:26.828 --> 54:29.701
have some reservations
about me...

54:29.744 --> 54:33.574
or may have heard some things
that you found disturbing.

54:33.618 --> 54:36.055
I would like to clear
all of that up.

54:36.098 --> 54:38.753
You guys know me.

54:38.797 --> 54:42.627
Doug, I have known you since,
what, third grade?

54:42.670 --> 54:45.282
Darlene, we have worked together
for 11 years.

54:46.979 --> 54:49.198
I am still that same person.

54:49.242 --> 54:51.288
I can promise you that.

54:51.331 --> 54:53.333
With me, what you see
is what you get.

54:54.856 --> 54:56.075
You bitch!

54:57.206 --> 54:58.077
Susan...

55:02.647 --> 55:05.432
After everything that
I've done for you.

55:05.476 --> 55:06.825
This is how you repay me?

55:06.868 --> 55:08.957
By sleeping with my husband?!

55:09.001 --> 55:10.611
I didn't, I swear.

55:10.655 --> 55:13.353
He came home and he started
packing his bags.

55:13.397 --> 55:15.137
He said that the two of you
were in love...

55:15.181 --> 55:16.617
and that this is a new
beginning.

55:16.661 --> 55:18.271
That is not true,
that's not true!

55:18.315 --> 55:19.490
I swear that's not true.

55:19.533 --> 55:23.276
Nothing is ever true
with you, Mary!

55:23.320 --> 55:26.584
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

55:26.627 --> 55:30.022
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

55:37.159 --> 55:38.944
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

56:33.085 --> 56:35.957
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

56:53.888 --> 56:55.716
I'm sorry, Charlie.

56:56.804 --> 56:58.850
I hope you know that.

57:00.112 --> 57:02.157
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

57:13.908 --> 57:15.562
Thanks for coming.

57:15.606 --> 57:16.868
Well, I gotta admit...

57:16.911 --> 57:19.740
I was a little surprised
when you called.

57:26.921 --> 57:30.447
Trevor Gates, your lawyer's
husband?

57:30.490 --> 57:31.796
Yes.

57:31.839 --> 57:33.275
And why are you just
sharing this now?

57:34.581 --> 57:37.758
I was embarrassed.

57:37.802 --> 57:39.847
And honestly, I didn't think
that Trevor was capable...

57:39.891 --> 57:41.327
of doing something like this.

57:41.370 --> 57:43.155
But now you do?

57:43.198 --> 57:45.505
He's been acting really weird.

57:45.549 --> 57:47.507
And you know when my house
was broken into...

57:47.551 --> 57:49.422
and that owl was broken?

57:49.466 --> 57:51.424
He commented on that owl
earlier that same day.

57:52.817 --> 57:57.822
Again, Mary, I've gotta ask.

57:57.865 --> 58:02.696
Why you didn't come forward
with this information sooner?

58:02.740 --> 58:04.045
I was advised not to.

58:04.089 --> 58:07.788
By Susan Gates?

58:07.832 --> 58:11.009
Have you ever stopped
to consider that maybe...

58:11.052 --> 58:13.185
the wife of the man
that you're sleeping with...

58:13.228 --> 58:15.666
might not have your best
interest in mind?

58:15.709 --> 58:16.928
I told you I didn't
sleep with him!

58:16.971 --> 58:18.451
So what?

58:18.495 --> 58:20.018
It sounds like she thinks
you did.

58:20.061 --> 58:21.889
Why would you...

58:24.152 --> 58:25.371
you heard about the
schoolboard meeting.

58:27.416 --> 58:28.548
So, then you already
knew about Trevor?

58:28.592 --> 58:30.115
Word gets around...

58:30.158 --> 58:32.160
and I find it interesting
that you waited...

58:32.204 --> 58:33.466
till the day after
the news broke...

58:33.510 --> 58:34.859
to mention any of this to me.

58:39.516 --> 58:41.953
But you'll still talk to him?

58:43.084 --> 58:44.782
Every possibility.

58:46.131 --> 58:48.002
I'll talk to him.

58:48.046 --> 58:50.527
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

58:59.318 --> 59:02.234
[ MUSIC FADES UP ]

59:09.110 --> 59:12.984
[ CALL RINGING ]

59:13.027 --> 59:14.115
[SUSAN OVER PHONE] You've reached the voicemail...

59:14.159 --> 59:16.074
of Susan Gates.

59:16.117 --> 59:17.989
If you're looking for
assistance contesting...

59:18.032 --> 59:20.121
a criminal charge, including
any traffic violations...

59:20.165 --> 59:22.167
please direct your call
to my office.

59:22.210 --> 59:24.604
Otherwise, go ahead and leave
a message after the tone.

59:24.648 --> 59:26.258
[ BEEP ]

59:26.301 --> 59:29.478
Hey, it's Mary.

59:31.568 --> 59:35.397
I know you said you never wanna
see me again and honestly...

59:35.441 --> 59:38.923
I can't blame you.

59:38.966 --> 59:42.361
I really screwed up
and I'm so sorry.

59:42.404 --> 59:47.671
I'm trying really hard
to make it right...

59:47.714 --> 59:51.936
but I'm just so scared.

59:51.979 --> 59:54.591
I could really use
my friend right now.

59:54.634 --> 59:57.463
Please call me.

01:00:07.255 --> 01:00:09.214
Hey.

01:00:11.172 --> 01:00:15.350
I'm really sorry I didn't
come sooner.

01:00:15.394 --> 01:00:18.092
Things have been really bad.

01:00:19.877 --> 01:00:22.793
God, I miss you so much.

01:00:26.361 --> 01:00:28.276
I don't know what to do.

01:00:30.365 --> 01:00:32.280
I lost you.

01:00:33.760 --> 01:00:35.632
Lost everyone.

01:00:36.894 --> 01:00:39.810
There's nobody left.

01:00:39.853 --> 01:00:41.855
That's not true.

01:00:44.075 --> 01:00:47.774
I'm sorry. I'll go.

01:00:47.818 --> 01:00:49.689
You don't have to.

01:00:51.560 --> 01:00:53.693
I didn't think you'd want
to see me.

01:00:53.737 --> 01:00:55.564
Why not? Because...

01:00:56.914 --> 01:00:58.916
because of what happened.

01:00:58.959 --> 01:01:00.918
Crystal told you, right?

01:01:04.878 --> 01:01:06.314
I'm so sorry.

01:01:06.358 --> 01:01:09.404
This may sound unmotherly...

01:01:09.448 --> 01:01:14.540
but your relationship with my
son is between you and him.

01:01:14.583 --> 01:01:17.369
I still view you as family.

01:01:17.412 --> 01:01:20.720
But for you to find out
about this now.

01:01:20.764 --> 01:01:22.069
And Crystal.

01:01:22.113 --> 01:01:23.157
Crystal already knew.

01:01:24.202 --> 01:01:25.943
But...

01:01:25.986 --> 01:01:28.641
but it had only happened once.

01:01:28.685 --> 01:01:32.297
And... nothing really happened.

01:01:32.340 --> 01:01:36.910
I mean, yeah, we kissed...
but that was it.

01:01:36.954 --> 01:01:38.956
It was just a mistake.

01:01:38.999 --> 01:01:41.567
It's okay. It's just that...

01:01:41.610 --> 01:01:44.526
Susan was taking Trevor's car...

01:01:44.570 --> 01:01:46.441
so he was cooped up
at the house...

01:01:46.485 --> 01:01:49.183
and he couldn't write there
so he would come over and...

01:01:49.227 --> 01:01:51.359
Charlie was always gone, so...

01:01:52.534 --> 01:01:54.667
we became close.

01:01:54.711 --> 01:01:57.322
But just as friends.

01:01:57.365 --> 01:02:00.151
And then Charlie missed
our anniversary and...

01:02:00.194 --> 01:02:02.980
it was just a mistake.

01:02:09.203 --> 01:02:12.076
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:02:20.519 --> 01:02:22.564
I remember the first time
he met you.

01:02:24.218 --> 01:02:27.744
I'd never seen him so happy.

01:02:27.787 --> 01:02:31.486
He said he'd found the girl
he was going to marry.

01:02:31.530 --> 01:02:33.967
Well, he had just broken
his front teeth...

01:02:34.011 --> 01:02:36.927
and he was high on
painkillers, so...

01:02:36.970 --> 01:02:40.321
Maybe...

01:02:40.365 --> 01:02:45.805
but they wore off and his
love for you never did.

01:02:45.849 --> 01:02:49.374
And I can tell that your love
never wore off either.

01:02:51.593 --> 01:02:53.552
I really loved him.

01:02:53.595 --> 01:02:55.206
I know.

01:02:57.469 --> 01:03:00.254
Do you think Crystal
believes that?

01:03:00.298 --> 01:03:01.778
Maybe you should tell her.

01:03:02.822 --> 01:03:04.824
I've tried.

01:03:04.868 --> 01:03:08.001
Maybe you should try again.

01:03:16.314 --> 01:03:19.404
[ SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES ]

01:03:24.322 --> 01:03:26.890
[ PHONE RINGING ]

01:03:30.067 --> 01:03:31.764
Susan.

01:03:31.808 --> 01:03:33.766
[SUSAN OVER PHONE]
I got your message.

01:03:33.810 --> 01:03:37.857
Thank you so much
for calling me back.

01:03:37.901 --> 01:03:41.818
I want you to know, I didn't
mean for any of this to happen.

01:03:41.861 --> 01:03:44.081
What I did was...

01:03:44.124 --> 01:03:45.865
awful.

01:03:45.909 --> 01:03:48.041
But I want our friendship
to stay alive.

01:03:48.085 --> 01:03:49.869
No matter what.

01:03:49.913 --> 01:03:51.523
[SUSAN OVER PHONE]
The cops came by earlier...

01:03:51.566 --> 01:03:53.655
looking for Trevor.

01:03:53.699 --> 01:03:58.704
I know, they found
out about everything.

01:03:58.747 --> 01:04:00.445
That's actually one
of the things...

01:04:00.488 --> 01:04:02.273
I wanted to clear up with you.

01:04:02.316 --> 01:04:05.102
[SUSAN OVER PHONE]
But, Mary, it wasn't him.

01:04:05.145 --> 01:04:07.321
I know, I-I just thought...

01:04:07.365 --> 01:04:09.149
[SUSAN OVER PHONE]
You were right.

01:04:09.193 --> 01:04:10.716
There was a traffic camera
near the beach house.

01:04:10.759 --> 01:04:12.413
Did it get anything?

01:04:12.457 --> 01:04:14.198
I'm sending you the picture
right now.

01:04:14.241 --> 01:04:15.895
I wanna go to the beach house
right away...

01:04:15.939 --> 01:04:17.723
and see what else the cops
might have missed.

01:04:17.766 --> 01:04:20.030
Of course. [ PHONE CHIMES ]

01:04:20.073 --> 01:04:23.555
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:04:29.300 --> 01:04:31.476
I'll meet you there.

01:04:31.519 --> 01:04:33.347
[ MUSIC CHANGES ]

01:04:41.355 --> 01:04:44.532
I visited Charlie today.

01:04:46.447 --> 01:04:48.972
You should visit him sometime.

01:04:52.497 --> 01:04:55.195
Mary was there.

01:04:55.239 --> 01:04:57.023
Not alone, I bet.

01:04:57.067 --> 01:04:59.939
She was.

01:04:59.983 --> 01:05:02.637
And she told me
all about her fling.

01:05:04.770 --> 01:05:07.947
No point keeping it a secret
anymore, is there?

01:05:07.991 --> 01:05:10.558
Sounds like nothing
really happened.

01:05:10.602 --> 01:05:13.474
He just came by a lot.

01:05:14.823 --> 01:05:17.870
Charlie's lying in the ground...

01:05:17.914 --> 01:05:22.222
and Mary is lying while standing
right on top of him.

01:05:22.266 --> 01:05:24.094
You don't know that, Crystal.

01:05:26.313 --> 01:05:27.532
I saw them, Mom.

01:05:27.575 --> 01:05:29.273
Mary said...

01:05:29.316 --> 01:05:32.319
he just came by her house
and only to write.

01:05:32.363 --> 01:05:35.366
Mary says a lot,
but I saw them...

01:05:35.409 --> 01:05:38.586
and they weren't writing
and they weren't at home.

01:05:38.630 --> 01:05:40.588
They were at the beach house.

01:05:40.632 --> 01:05:42.373
The beach house?

01:05:42.416 --> 01:05:43.591
Yes.

01:05:43.635 --> 01:05:44.810
Why didn't you say anything?

01:05:44.853 --> 01:05:46.638
Because you always said...

01:05:46.681 --> 01:05:49.336
that their relationship
was their business.

01:05:49.380 --> 01:05:51.860
So, instead of talking
to Charlie about it...

01:05:51.904 --> 01:05:53.471
I talked to Mary.

01:05:53.514 --> 01:05:55.690
I encouraged her to talk to him.

01:05:55.734 --> 01:05:58.911
I... I thought they could
work through it.

01:05:58.955 --> 01:06:01.435
You don't think I give her
the benefit of the doubt?

01:06:01.479 --> 01:06:03.089
Well, I did...

01:06:03.133 --> 01:06:04.395
and look what happened?

01:06:04.438 --> 01:06:07.876
Crystal, you can't blame
yourself.

01:06:07.920 --> 01:06:09.095
Yes...

01:06:09.139 --> 01:06:10.575
I can.

01:06:49.962 --> 01:06:52.182
I knew you'd come by eventually.

01:06:52.225 --> 01:06:54.053
I was waiting for you.

01:06:54.097 --> 01:06:55.141
What are you doing here?

01:06:55.185 --> 01:06:57.491
Don't you know?

01:06:57.535 --> 01:06:59.015
I did it.

01:07:00.407 --> 01:07:02.453
I left my wife.

01:07:02.496 --> 01:07:04.759
I told her everything.

01:07:04.803 --> 01:07:06.457
I never asked you
to do that, Trevor.

01:07:06.500 --> 01:07:08.459
Because you're a good person.

01:07:08.502 --> 01:07:11.766
And just like me you're just a...

01:07:11.810 --> 01:07:14.856
a victim of bad timing.

01:07:14.900 --> 01:07:17.033
You just married
the wrong person.

01:07:17.076 --> 01:07:21.211
I gave Susan my soul...

01:07:21.254 --> 01:07:24.953
and it wasn't enough for her.

01:07:24.997 --> 01:07:26.607
She's cold.

01:07:26.651 --> 01:07:29.784
Mary, she is, and frankly,
so's Charlie.

01:07:29.828 --> 01:07:32.265
I'm sorry, I'm sorry,
I shouldn't have said that.

01:07:32.309 --> 01:07:34.615
That's just the thing though
about me is that...

01:07:34.659 --> 01:07:35.834
I don't hold back.

01:07:35.877 --> 01:07:36.878
Not like Susan.

01:07:36.922 --> 01:07:41.100
I go after what I want.

01:07:41.144 --> 01:07:42.667
And I wanna be with you.

01:07:42.710 --> 01:07:44.756
I don't wanna be with you.

01:07:44.799 --> 01:07:47.628
That's not what you said
that night.

01:07:47.672 --> 01:07:49.674
When you brought me
into you bedroom.

01:07:49.717 --> 01:07:52.024
That night was a mistake.
We were drinking...

01:07:52.068 --> 01:07:53.547
You invited me over.

01:07:53.591 --> 01:07:55.941
You offered me wine.

01:07:55.984 --> 01:07:59.640
You told me...
leave your writing at home.

01:07:59.684 --> 01:08:01.947
You were... you were warm
and you were kind.

01:08:01.990 --> 01:08:03.383
I just needed someone.

01:08:03.427 --> 01:08:05.472
And you don't now? We were friends.

01:08:05.516 --> 01:08:08.867
What happened between us
wasn't friends.

01:08:10.303 --> 01:08:13.437
What happened between us
was passion.

01:08:15.395 --> 01:08:17.571
Nothing happened.

01:08:17.615 --> 01:08:20.444
Nothing will happen.

01:08:20.487 --> 01:08:21.575
Ever.

01:08:22.794 --> 01:08:25.318
Yes, it will.No.

01:08:25.362 --> 01:08:27.451
This is not one of your
stories, Trevor.

01:08:27.493 --> 01:08:29.148
You don't get to write
the ending.

01:08:31.845 --> 01:08:35.111
I gave up my home, my wife.

01:08:35.154 --> 01:08:39.115
I did everything for you,
and this is how you treat me?

01:08:39.158 --> 01:08:40.332
You led me on.

01:08:40.377 --> 01:08:42.509
Made me fall in love with you.

01:08:42.553 --> 01:08:44.946
You're no better than Susan.

01:08:44.990 --> 01:08:48.036
Just playing games
with people's emotions.

01:08:48.080 --> 01:08:49.125
No, no, of course not.

01:08:49.167 --> 01:08:50.734
You don't get to do that!

01:08:50.778 --> 01:08:52.997
You don't get to take me
into your bedroom...

01:08:53.041 --> 01:08:54.694
and then cast me aside like...

01:08:55.609 --> 01:08:57.176
Oh my god!

01:08:57.220 --> 01:08:59.483
Are you okay, are you okay,
can you move it?

01:08:59.526 --> 01:09:01.093
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:09:01.136 --> 01:09:02.964
Let me go!

01:09:03.008 --> 01:09:04.444
No, no, no, I'm sorry,
I'm sorry.

01:09:04.488 --> 01:09:07.055
I'm sorry. I just... I just...

01:09:07.099 --> 01:09:10.885
I can't control myself
when I'm around you.

01:09:10.929 --> 01:09:12.844
If you'll just...

01:09:12.886 --> 01:09:15.846
just give me a chance,
I could make you so happy.

01:09:15.890 --> 01:09:18.763
I could, just please give me
a chance, please?

01:09:18.805 --> 01:09:20.068
Where were you?

01:09:20.112 --> 01:09:21.721
With you, always with you.No.

01:09:23.506 --> 01:09:26.249
The night that Charlie
was killed.

01:09:26.292 --> 01:09:27.728
Where were you?

01:09:33.212 --> 01:09:38.216
You think that I killed Charlie?

01:09:38.261 --> 01:09:41.481
That is rich!

01:09:41.524 --> 01:09:45.268
No, no, no, no, I didn't...

01:09:45.310 --> 01:09:48.053
I didn't kill your precious
Charlie.

01:09:48.095 --> 01:09:50.621
I didn't have to.

01:09:50.663 --> 01:09:53.667
I already had you,
you know that.

01:09:53.711 --> 01:09:57.367
It is just like you
to stab him in the back.

01:09:57.410 --> 01:09:58.890
Let me go!

01:09:58.933 --> 01:10:00.152
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:10:00.196 --> 01:10:02.372
Trevor, you're hurting me.

01:10:02.415 --> 01:10:04.722
That's all you've ever done
is hurt me.

01:10:04.765 --> 01:10:07.942
I'm just beginning to see you
for the lying...

01:10:07.986 --> 01:10:10.728
manipulative woman that you are! Please...

01:10:10.771 --> 01:10:13.731
I can't believe I ever thought
that you were worthy...

01:10:13.774 --> 01:10:15.515
of my love.

01:10:15.559 --> 01:10:17.300
Susan was right about you...

01:10:18.997 --> 01:10:23.001
[ BREATHING HEAVY ]

01:10:23.044 --> 01:10:24.481
Well, that was out of character.

01:10:24.524 --> 01:10:26.439
He just snapped.

01:10:26.483 --> 01:10:29.442
Yes, he did.

01:10:31.096 --> 01:10:32.837
Are you okay?

01:10:34.621 --> 01:10:36.493
I'm okay.

01:10:36.536 --> 01:10:38.016
I just...

01:10:38.059 --> 01:10:40.888
Wow.

01:10:40.932 --> 01:10:42.673
I just need to get some water
or something.

01:10:48.244 --> 01:10:50.246
[ GROANING ]

01:10:55.947 --> 01:10:57.862
If you're looking for this...

01:10:57.905 --> 01:11:00.865
then you're even dumber
than I thought.

01:11:17.011 --> 01:11:18.970
Forgive me.

01:11:28.936 --> 01:11:30.764
[ GUN FIRES ]

01:11:30.808 --> 01:11:33.811
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:11:36.292 --> 01:11:38.729
Oh my god.

01:11:38.772 --> 01:11:40.861
He woke up and I've never
seen him like that.

01:11:40.905 --> 01:11:43.734
He was so angry and he
reached for me!

01:11:43.777 --> 01:11:45.475
Are you okay, did he hurt you?

01:11:45.518 --> 01:11:46.998
He grabbed me!

01:11:47.041 --> 01:11:48.695
I thought he was gonna kill me!

01:11:48.739 --> 01:11:50.436
Oh, my god. Oh, Susan.

01:11:51.916 --> 01:11:53.961
Maybe he did kill Charlie.

01:11:56.181 --> 01:11:58.488
But... but what about Crystal?

01:11:58.531 --> 01:12:00.577
I guess I was wrong.

01:12:01.578 --> 01:12:03.319
I'm so sorry.

01:12:03.362 --> 01:12:04.842
I'm so sorry. It's okay, it's okay.

01:12:04.885 --> 01:12:07.540
I'm so sorry.

01:12:07.584 --> 01:12:10.630
I thought I knew what was best,
but I was wrong.

01:12:10.674 --> 01:12:13.633
Like always.

01:12:13.677 --> 01:12:17.289
And I thought you knew
what was best.

01:12:17.333 --> 01:12:19.900
You never told on me.

01:12:19.944 --> 01:12:22.338
Never told on me for anything.

01:12:27.299 --> 01:12:29.606
Thank you for coming.

01:12:29.649 --> 01:12:31.390
I was hoping we could talk
about my...

01:12:31.434 --> 01:12:33.740
Are you gonna tell the truth
this time or what?

01:12:33.784 --> 01:12:36.439
See, last time we spoke, you
said you didn't know anything.

01:12:36.482 --> 01:12:39.703
But ever since then, all I keep
hearing are stories that...

01:12:39.746 --> 01:12:42.662
you found Mary or you saw her
in the act.

01:12:42.706 --> 01:12:48.581
I didn't actually see them
at the beach house, but...

01:12:48.625 --> 01:12:52.150
but I heard somebody inside
and they were...

01:12:52.193 --> 01:12:54.413
they were having...

01:12:54.457 --> 01:12:56.110
you know.

01:12:56.154 --> 01:12:57.634
I thought it was them.

01:12:57.677 --> 01:12:59.113
What did you see?

01:12:59.157 --> 01:13:01.028
I saw a car.

01:13:01.072 --> 01:13:03.944
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:13:08.949 --> 01:13:12.126
I don't understand.
It had to be him.

01:13:12.170 --> 01:13:15.434
But... Crystal, she...
the traffic cameras.

01:13:15.478 --> 01:13:17.393
Well, maybe she saw something.

01:13:17.436 --> 01:13:20.047
You should call her and see
if she can meet us.

01:13:20.091 --> 01:13:21.397
Okay. And Mary...

01:13:22.876 --> 01:13:26.227
hopefully this will all
be over soon.

01:13:32.146 --> 01:13:35.019
[ OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:13:37.804 --> 01:13:40.807
The call keeps dropping.

01:13:40.851 --> 01:13:43.201
Do you want to call the police
while I do this?

01:13:43.244 --> 01:13:45.421
Oh, sure, okay.

01:13:51.688 --> 01:13:53.080
Jesus.

01:13:53.124 --> 01:13:54.430
Oh my god!

01:13:56.040 --> 01:13:57.476
[ GUN FIRES ]

01:14:05.484 --> 01:14:07.181
Are you okay?

01:14:10.402 --> 01:14:12.012
Did you get through to Crystal?

01:14:19.977 --> 01:14:22.153
It was her.

01:14:28.028 --> 01:14:30.901
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:14:37.908 --> 01:14:40.476
I really wish he hadn't
found that.

01:14:40.519 --> 01:14:41.999
It was you?

01:14:42.042 --> 01:14:46.220
Did you get through to Crystal?

01:14:46.264 --> 01:14:48.396
I sent her a text message,
she's on her way.

01:14:48.440 --> 01:14:51.791
You're a terrible liar, Mary.
I really wish you had, though.

01:14:51.835 --> 01:14:53.793
Would save me some trouble
later.

01:14:53.837 --> 01:14:56.361
[MARY] Why?

01:14:56.404 --> 01:14:58.929
Why Crystal?

01:14:58.972 --> 01:15:01.540
Because she saw too much.

01:15:01.584 --> 01:15:03.455
You know, it's funny...

01:15:03.499 --> 01:15:05.762
I thought that it was you
outside the house that night.

01:15:05.805 --> 01:15:08.808
And I was so impressed with
how well you kept it together...

01:15:08.852 --> 01:15:12.899
at dinner, but...
no, I was wrong again.

01:15:12.943 --> 01:15:14.858
Wrong nosey female relative.

01:15:14.901 --> 01:15:17.469
Thanks for the traffic
cam tip though.

01:15:17.513 --> 01:15:19.166
Real sloppy of me.

01:15:19.210 --> 01:15:20.646
You and Charlie?

01:15:20.690 --> 01:15:22.996
Don't insult me by acting
surprised.

01:15:23.040 --> 01:15:26.870
You knew that he was too much
for you to handle, Bookworm.

01:15:26.913 --> 01:15:28.393
You killed him.

01:15:28.436 --> 01:15:31.570
After the first time...
he wanted out.

01:15:31.614 --> 01:15:34.747
But you know Charlie, he was
never very good with words.

01:15:34.791 --> 01:15:37.097
His actions said otherwise.

01:15:37.141 --> 01:15:39.186
Until I showed up
at your little dinner.

01:15:39.230 --> 01:15:42.015
Now that... that was
the last straw.

01:15:42.059 --> 01:15:43.800
He was really gonna leave.

01:15:43.843 --> 01:15:45.715
You're a murderer.

01:15:45.758 --> 01:15:49.632
No, no, you are.

01:15:49.675 --> 01:15:52.722
And I made sure of that,
though you certainly helped.

01:15:52.765 --> 01:15:55.594
See, after Trevor convinced you
to put a kitchen knife...

01:15:55.638 --> 01:15:58.379
in your husband's back,
you got cold feet.

01:15:58.423 --> 01:16:00.077
But he was blackmailing you.

01:16:00.120 --> 01:16:03.254
So, you decided to take care
of that here.

01:16:03.297 --> 01:16:05.604
But before Trevor died,
he was able...

01:16:05.648 --> 01:16:07.650
to inflict one mortal wound.

01:16:07.693 --> 01:16:09.652
You took the knife.

01:16:09.695 --> 01:16:11.915
Yes, I did.

01:16:11.958 --> 01:16:16.049
And thanks for making
it so difficult.

01:16:16.093 --> 01:16:20.053
If you'd just left me alone for
five minutes in your kitchen...

01:16:20.097 --> 01:16:22.882
I wouldn't've had to break
your precious little owl.

01:16:22.926 --> 01:16:26.407
I trusted you.

01:16:26.451 --> 01:16:30.586
Now, these are pretty ironic
words coming from a woman...

01:16:30.629 --> 01:16:32.588
who slept with my husband.

01:16:32.631 --> 01:16:34.677
I never slept with him!

01:16:34.720 --> 01:16:37.418
Oh, wait, really?

01:16:37.462 --> 01:16:38.768
Never!

01:16:40.987 --> 01:16:44.425
Well, you weren't missing much.

01:16:44.469 --> 01:16:46.602
Susan, that was your husband.

01:16:47.820 --> 01:16:50.649
Everybody makes mistakes.

01:16:50.693 --> 01:16:53.347
Wait, think about this.

01:16:53.391 --> 01:16:54.653
You'll never get away with it.

01:16:54.697 --> 01:16:57.221
Have you not been paying
attention?

01:16:57.264 --> 01:16:59.789
I thought this through,
I figured it all out.

01:16:59.832 --> 01:17:01.747
It's a storybook ending.

01:17:01.791 --> 01:17:03.923
I would think that if anyone
would appreciate that...

01:17:03.967 --> 01:17:05.621
you would, Bookworm!

01:17:05.664 --> 01:17:07.318
Oh, and by the way...

01:17:07.361 --> 01:17:10.364
that was his real nickname
for you, not Little Owl.

01:17:10.408 --> 01:17:13.280
Please... it doesn't have
to be like this.

01:17:13.324 --> 01:17:15.108
I won't tell anybody.

01:17:15.152 --> 01:17:18.503
Well, that sounds like the
ending of one of Trevor's books.

01:17:18.546 --> 01:17:21.680
And there's a reason
that they don't sell.

01:17:21.724 --> 01:17:23.464
Too many loose ends.

01:17:23.508 --> 01:17:26.250
It's a shame that Crystal
couldn't join us.

01:17:26.293 --> 01:17:28.644
But still...

01:17:28.687 --> 01:17:30.863
I'll make sure it's nice
and tidy.

01:17:30.907 --> 01:17:31.995
[ PHONE CHIMES ]

01:17:34.998 --> 01:17:37.609
Crystal wants to know
if you can chat.

01:17:37.653 --> 01:17:39.176
Should I tell her that
you're unavailable?

01:17:39.219 --> 01:17:40.307
Or maybe...

01:17:40.351 --> 01:17:43.223
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:17:46.662 --> 01:17:47.575
Damn it.

01:17:55.583 --> 01:17:58.456
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

01:18:10.424 --> 01:18:13.340
Police only have one
suspect, Mary...

01:18:13.384 --> 01:18:15.603
they'll make the evidence
fit the crime.

01:18:36.146 --> 01:18:37.234
[ GUN COCKS ]

01:18:42.282 --> 01:18:44.154
Can't crawl away from me,
Bookworm.

01:18:57.384 --> 01:18:59.343
I liked you once...

01:18:59.386 --> 01:19:01.998
and a part of me wishes I could
just shoot you in the face.

01:19:02.041 --> 01:19:05.044
But no... a suicide won't do.

01:19:05.088 --> 01:19:07.394
It needs to look like you
had time to bleed out...

01:19:07.438 --> 01:19:09.135
after you killed Trevor.

01:19:09.179 --> 01:19:12.095
And then Crystal found you.

01:19:12.138 --> 01:19:15.881
And maybe I'll save
the suicide for her.

01:19:15.925 --> 01:19:18.449
I really am sorry.

01:19:21.191 --> 01:19:24.672
I hear that gut shots
are terribly painful.

01:19:26.283 --> 01:19:27.588
Please...

01:19:27.632 --> 01:19:29.852
Thank you... for begging.

01:19:29.895 --> 01:19:31.505
I really appreciate... [ CAR DOOR SLAMS ]

01:19:34.944 --> 01:19:36.597
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

01:19:36.641 --> 01:19:39.252
Perfect timing.

01:19:39.296 --> 01:19:41.385
Maybe it doesn't have to be
a suicide after all.

01:19:41.428 --> 01:19:42.603
[ PHONE CHIMES ]

01:19:44.823 --> 01:19:45.998
Agh!

01:19:50.786 --> 01:19:53.484
Two lovers killed
by the same blade.

01:19:53.527 --> 01:19:54.833
Now, that's a storybook ending.

01:19:54.877 --> 01:19:56.530
Police! Drop your weapon!

01:19:56.574 --> 01:19:58.489
Do it! No, Mary, don't.

01:19:58.532 --> 01:20:00.708
[MARY] No, no.

01:20:00.752 --> 01:20:03.146
I don't think I will.

01:20:17.638 --> 01:20:19.858
Anything you say can and will
be held against you...

01:20:19.902 --> 01:20:21.599
in a court of law. You have
the right to an attorney.

01:20:21.642 --> 01:20:23.209
I am an attorney.

01:20:23.253 --> 01:20:25.081
Whatever, lady.

01:20:34.046 --> 01:20:37.833
[ PHONE RINGING ]

01:20:40.313 --> 01:20:42.315
Yes, sir?

01:20:42.359 --> 01:20:46.363
Yeah, forensics has it now.

01:20:46.406 --> 01:20:50.584
Seems she stashed the knife
in a paint can and then fled.

01:20:51.934 --> 01:20:52.935
Yeah...

01:20:52.978 --> 01:20:55.067
that was my mistake.

01:20:55.111 --> 01:20:57.853
I'm gonna have to call you back.

01:21:07.166 --> 01:21:09.168
Thank you, guys.

01:21:09.212 --> 01:21:11.475
You saved my life.

01:21:11.518 --> 01:21:13.520
How did you know where I was?

01:21:13.564 --> 01:21:15.392
You weren't at home, so...

01:21:15.435 --> 01:21:18.177
Just exploring every
possibility, right?

01:21:18.221 --> 01:21:20.179
Funny you mention that.

01:21:20.223 --> 01:21:22.007
I think I found your
murder weapon.

01:21:22.051 --> 01:21:25.184
And our murderer,
from the looks of it.

01:21:25.228 --> 01:21:28.927
You may have a few more
court dates coming up soon.

01:21:28.971 --> 01:21:32.626
If so, I suggest finding
better representation.

01:21:34.672 --> 01:21:37.501
Is that your version
of an apology?

01:21:37.544 --> 01:21:39.982
No.

01:21:40.025 --> 01:21:43.594
Sorry you had to go through
this, Mary.

01:21:43.637 --> 01:21:46.336
And I'm sorry we didn't
trust you.

01:21:46.379 --> 01:21:48.381
It's okay...

01:21:48.425 --> 01:21:50.514
everybody makes mistakes.

01:21:50.557 --> 01:21:54.213
If you need a place to stay
we can arrange that.

